config BR2_PACKAGE_MUNT
	bool "munt"
	depends on BR2_INSTALL_LIBSTDCPP
	depends on BR2_TOOLCHAIN_HAS_THREADS
	select BR2_PACKAGE_ALSA_LIB
	help
	  Munt: a multi-platform software synthesiser emulating Roland's
	  pre-GM MIDI devices (MT-32, CM-32L, CM-64, LAPC-I). Stock ships
	  its console ALSA-sequencer daemon as /usr/sbin/mt32d (P0.3
	  inventory: docs/stock-inventory/binaries-needed-full.txt) --
	  spawned on demand by MidiLink (package/midilink) whenever a core
	  requests MT-32/CM-32 emulation instead of a real MT-32 or a
	  FluidSynth soundfont. Buildroot has no upstream "munt" package,
	  so this builds it from the project's own source (P3.8).

	  This package builds:
	    - libmt32emu (the emulation library, LGPL-2.1+) via munt's own
	      CMake project, restricted to the mt32emu/ subdirectory so
	      the Qt-based mt32emu_qt GUI and the win32 driver are never
	      even configured.
	    - mt32d (the headless console ALSA daemon, also LGPL-2.1+ per
	      its own file header) from mt32emu_alsadrv/src/{console,
	      alsadrv,wav}.cpp, linked against the freshly staged
	      libmt32emu + this system's alsa-lib -- NOT against any
	      vendored ALSA bits (there are none here to vendor; unlike
	      MidiLink upstream, mt32emu_alsadrv already expects a system
	      alsa-lib). xmt32 (the X11 GUI counterpart in the same source
	      directory) is deliberately never built: it needs
	      libX11/libXt/libXpm, none of which this headless image
	      ships, and mt32d alone is everything MidiLink's "MUNT"
	      uartmode shells out to.

	  ROM NOTE: the actual Roland MT32_CONTROL.ROM / MT32_PCM.ROM (and
	  CM-32L equivalents) are Roland's copyrighted firmware. Stock does
	  NOT bundle them -- this package does not fetch, extract, or embed
	  them either (G6). mt32d takes the ROM directory as a `-f <path>`
	  command-line argument at runtime (MidiLink passes stock's default
	  of /media/fat/linux/mt32-rom-data via MidiLink.INI's
	  MUNT_ROM_PATH); users who own real MT-32/CM-32 hardware supply
	  their own dumped ROM files at that path, exactly as in stock. See
	  docs/midi-mt32-parity.md.

	  https://github.com/munt/munt

comment "munt needs a toolchain w/ C++ and threads"
	depends on !BR2_INSTALL_LIBSTDCPP || !BR2_TOOLCHAIN_HAS_THREADS
